Jefferies Hires Old for Real Estate Investment-Banking Unit

-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 
2011-04-28T13:39:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/jefferies-hires-old-for-real-estate-investment-banking-unit.html
Jefferies Group Inc. (JEF) , the
investment bank that has been expanding since the financial
crisis, hired Michael Old as a managing director in the firm’s
real estate investment-banking unit.  Old was previously a managing director in the European real
estate structured-finance group at Bank of America Merrill
Lynch, New York-based Jefferies said today in a statement. He
will be based in London.  Jefferies is expanding its London investment-banking
division after the firm hired Simon Hampton as European head of
real estate, gaming and lodging investment banking in October
and Steffen Doyle as head of European lodging and gaming
investment banking in February. Hampton and Doyle joined
Jefferies from  Bank of America Corp. (BAC)   “Michael is a highly experienced real estate banker with a
proven track record in real estate structured finance, debt
capital raising and balance sheet restructuring,” Hampton said
in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
